cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.ET, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) because it focuses on the implementation of a novel architecture for CNNs on a resource-constrained MPSoC with CPU and FPGA. It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) because it deals with visual recognition using CNNs on datasets such as CIFAR-10, CIFAR-100, and SVHN. Additionally, it may belong to cs.ET (Embedded Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) because it deals with the implementation of CNNs on embedded devices and the decision-making process for using shallow or deep networks. Finally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because it deals with the use of neural networks for visual recognition.
